    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Gene Upshaw, the executive director of the National Football League players' union, said yesterday that a separate area apart from the locker room should be provided for the news media after games splayers would not be required to participate in media interviews unless fully clothed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: Gene Upshaw, the executive director of the National Football League players' union, said yesterday that a separate area apart from the locker room should be provided for the news media after games splayers would not be required to participate in media interviews unless fully clothed.</p>
        <p>Gene Upshaw, the executive director of the National Football League players' union, said yesterday that a separate area apart from the locker room should be provided for the news media after games splayers would not be required to participate in media interviews unless fully clothed.</p>
        <p>Upshaw's statement was the latest comment in a controversy that has seen charges by a female reporter for The Boston Herald that she was sexually harassed by Patriot players and a fine of about $30,000 imposed of Sam Wyche, the Bengal coach, for closing his team's locker room to a feamle reporter. (AP)  SPORTS PEOPLE: FOOTBALL</p>
